CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1960, pg. 2 reads: "Democratic Teammates - Among Democrats in Pittsburgh this week in a gigantic pep rally to aid the drive of Senator Kennedy for the U.S. Presidency were, left to right; Philadelphian Mayor Richardson Dilworth and U.S .Senator Joseph Clark; former Indian Ambassador Chester Bowles, Democratic Convention platform speaker, and Mrs. Louis J. Reizenstein of Pittsburgh, who, together with Mayor Dilworth, chairs the statewide Citizens for Kennedy movement. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Philadelphia Mayor Richardson Dilworth, Senator Joseph Clark, former Indian Ambassador Chester Bowles, and Florence Reizenstein, standing in Penn-Sheraton Hotel for Kennedy Conference on Urban Renewal
